## 0.0.2

- Added flag support for regex compilation
    - case insensitive matching,
    - unicode character classes
    - leftmost longest semantics
    - . to match \n characters
- Support more escape sequences
- Parse regexes with non-capturing and named groups (implemention still ignores grouping constructs)
- Performance improvements
    - search for first character using boolean[] array for valid first characters
    - customizable character distributions to determine whether initial character searches are useful
    - optimize backward scans for finding regex start when first character cannot contained in a proper infix
    - use power of two sized byteclasses
    - unify handling of unicode needles with non-unicode
    - store match results on the `Matcher`, rather than creating `MatchResult` object per match.
- Bug fixes
    - parser edge cases
    - reduce inconsistencies with the standard library and document remaining ones
- More thorough testing
    - roughly doubled the number of example based tests
    - snapshot testing to track which compiled classes are changed by any given code change

## 0.0.1

- Initial release
